# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OUT LOUD — matches the AEF-Courses convention.
#
# mp3 audio files ARE committed and pushed. Students need
# playback when they practice at home, and the deployed
# GitHub Pages site is how they get it. This is deliberate.
#
# PDFs (student book / teacher's book / workbook pages) are
# NOT pushed — those stay on the Desktop only.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Copyrighted textbook print material — kept locally, never pushed
*.pdf

# ── Student recordings (Fluency Log) — private, never pushed ──
lesson-*.webm
*fluency*/

# ── Node dependencies (regenerable) ──
node_modules/

# ── OS junk ──
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
._*

# ── Manual timestamped backups (git history replaces these) ──
index_backup_*.html
index_2*.html
*_backup_*.html
*.bak
